<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Princedale to acquire Hillsdown companies
for maximum Pounds 9.2m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JEAN MARSHALL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PRINCEDALE Group, the USM-quoted marketing and design consultancy, plans to
form a new industrial division through the acquisition of Colloids, Hallam
Plastics and Hallmark Contract Hire from Hillsdown Holdings and other
minority holders.
The initial cost is Pounds 7.65m, which may increase to a maximum Pounds
9.15m.
At the same time, Princedale announced pre-tax losses of Pounds 71,000
(Pounds 326,000 profits) for the six months to March 31. Turnover fell to
Pounds 4.47m (Pounds 6.37m) and there were losses per share of 0.01p (0.06p
earnings).
The acquisitions are being funded as to Pounds 3.49m by the issue to the
vendors of new consolidated ordinary shares at 25p per share, Pounds 3.45m
by the issue of 7 per cent fixed secured loan notes, and Pounds 700,000 in
cash.
A placing and open offer of 16m new consolidated ordinary shares,
underwritten by Guinness Mahon, will raise about Pounds 4m, of which Pounds
1.6m is for Princedale.
Princedale's existing ordinary shares will be consolidated on the basis of
one consolidated ordinary share for every 20 existing ordinary shares.
Shareholders may apply under the open offer on the basis of five offer
shares for every eight consolidated ordinary shares resulting from the
capital reorganisation.
Princedale's current account period will run for 15 months.
</TEXT>
