<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JUN 93 / Observer: Invisible man
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Hans van den Broek, the EC commissioner for external political relations,
failed to show much sign of the Community's much-vaunted transparency
yesterday. He turned up at the Commission's offices in London in the back of
a large limo with heavily blacked-out windows.
When questioned about his lack of visibility, the ever-cheerful Van den
Broek quipped that this was just the car he used for shopping.
</TEXT>
