</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW FISHER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sales staff, traders, and analysts in banks and securities houses are used
to having their performance monitored - but probably not to the extent
envisaged by Synchronocity, a London-based software house.
At a glance, managers using its Profit-Line system can see on screen the
cost, performance and profit ratios of their employees and decide how best
to direct their efforts and make them most productive. The information can
be viewed in grid format, against time taken for work, or ranked by
performance, with the analysis carried out hourly, daily, weekly and monthly
and targetted to sales employee, customer, analyst, trader or deal.
Synchronicity claims one decision made with Profit-Line's analysis could
save far more than its Pounds 10,000 cost. Synchronicity: UK, 071 729 6404.
