government reshuffle, said he had been impressed by Brixton, the oldest
prison in London. 'Being in prison in Brixton isn't a picnic,' he said. 'But
nor should being in prison be a picnic.' He intended to continue with
privatisation because he believed the private sector had a role to play in
running prisons.
