FT  04 JUN 93 / Global debate to be held in Manchester
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MANCHESTER yesterday officially took over from Rio de Janeiro as the venue
for global debate on how to reconcile industrial development with
environmental issues. There will be two events instead of the single
marathon run last year at Rio.
A government-run conference in September will address the implemention of
policies agreed at last year's Earth Summit in Rio, while a wider 10-day
Global Forum involving local authorities, industry and commerce,
environmental lobby groups and the general public will take place in June
next year.
It is hoped that Mr Al Gore, the US vice-president, will attend the forum.
The government will pay for the September event but the Pounds 4m funding of
the forum has yet to be finalised.
