<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JUN 93 / Shell staff refuse new contracts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WORKERS AT Shell's Haven oil refinery in Essex are refusing to accept
individual contracts of employment and union derecognition, it was announced
yesterday. Mr Fred Higgs, TGWU national secretary for the oil industry, said
that Shell was 'attempting to deny our 470 members their basic right to
trade union representation and is using the threat of redundancy as a weapon
to intimidate the workforce into signing individual contracts'.
Yesterday Shell confirmed that it was going ahead with derecognition at the
Haven refinery for wage bargaining purposes, though workers can still belong
to unions. It also announced it would impose compulsory redundancies by the
end of next year.
