Two-day talks between Timex US, the UK company management and union
leaders result in peasce plan involving lay-offs by rotation, wage
freeze and 10 per cent cut in benefits
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
February 14
Mass meeting rejects plan
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
February 15
Company refuses to take back strikers who were ready to return 'under
protest'
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
February 17
Peace plan again rejected at mass meeting. Dismissal notices issued
and other workers recruited. New strike begins
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
May 17
End of 90 days of the strike. Company can re-hire selectively without
danger of legal action aginst it
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
June 3
A new negotiated peace deal is rejected unanimously by the
membership
