FT  04 JUN 93 / Inquiry launched as seven die in tanker crash
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AN official inquiry is to be launched after seven people were killed and two
were missing feared dead in a tanker collision in thick fog off the Belgian
coast early yesterday morning.
Four Britons and two Irishmen are among the dead or missing. The rest are
from Sierra Leone.
The British Petroleum-owned tanker British Trent (above), with a 24,000
tonne cargo of petrol, collided with the Panamanian-registered cargo ship
Western Winner. The tanker's hull was punctured, releasing blazing petrol
into the sea.
BP will conduct a separate investigation.
