FT  03 JUN 93 / International Company News: Newbridge Networks record
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NEWBRIDGE NETWORKS, an Ottawa-based data system equipment maker, posted
record sales and profit for the year ended April 30. It attributed the rise
mainly to large orders from international telephone companies, writes Robert
Gibbens in Montreal.
Sales jumped 70 per cent to CDollars 307m (USDollars 241.7m), while profit
advanced to CDollars 60m, or CDollars 1.63 a share, well ahead of the
CDollars 9.7m, or 28 cents a share, reported a year earlier.
Fourth-quarter profit rose to CDollars 25.5m, or 65 cents, compared with
CDollars 4.7m, or 13 cents, a year earlier, on revenue of CDollars 100m,
against CDollars 52m.
Eight-year-old Newbridge, which specialises in multiplexers for data and
computer networks, said its order book had risen steadily over eight
consecutive quarters.
