<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 93 / UK Company News: SW Wood ahead and pays Pounds 2.5m for A
Gait
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SW WOOD, the specialist printing and packaging business previously involved
in metal trading, is acquiring Albert Gait Holdings and its subsidiaries for
an initial Pounds 2.51m.
The acquisition is part of Wood's policy of expansion in the printing and
packaging industry.
The initial Pounds 2.51m payment is to be satisfied by the issue of 2.39m
ordinary shares worth 70p each, making Pounds 1.68m, plus Pounds 837,500 in
cash. These payments rely on Gait achieving pre-tax profits of Pounds
500,000 in the year to June 30 and net assets of Pounds 1.7m.
Further cash consideration to a maximum of Pounds 506,250 will be due if
adjusted profits for the year to June 30 1994 exceed Pounds 335,000.
Grimsby-based Gait is involved in the printing and production of timetables
and handbooks, computerised typesetting, plate making and book and
stationery retailing.
Wood yesterday also announced sharply higher profits for the year to March
31. The pre-tax result of Pounds 1.02m compared with a Pounds 250,000
deficit previously (restated in accordance with the FRS 3 accounting
standard).
The directors have recommended payment of a final dividend of 0.75p, which
makes an increased total of 1.25p (0.25p).
Turnover for the 12 months jumped to Pounds 10.6m, including Pounds 909,000
from discontinued operations.
Sales of Pounds 5.24m in 1991-92 included Pounds 2.9m from discontinued
operations.
Shareholders' approval for the acquisition will be sought at an egm on July
2.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
