<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 93 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JOHANNESBURG gold shares finished off their lows but remained sharply down -
157, or 8.5 per cent lower at 1,699 - after the bullion price failed to
bounce from its overnight slide and anxious players marked down prices in
anticipation of heavy selling. Industrials were 14 off at 4,509 and the
overall index was 79, or 2 per cent, lower at 3,902.
